annotationA: Protein ORD; Essential for proper maintenance of sister-chromatid cohesion in both male and female meiosis. Mutations in ord cause premature separation of the sister chromatids in meiosis I and random segregation in both meiotic divisions. Required for chiasma maintenance in female meiosis. Mutations in ord reduce recombination in female meiosis
annotationB: Crossover suppressor on 2 of Manheim is a a Kleisin family member in the cohesin proteins. It interacts with cohesins such as SMC1 and SMC3 to promote synaptonemal complex assembly in female meiosis
